'''Ibrahim Maza''' ({{langx|ar|إبراهيم مازة}}; born 24 November 2005) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{German football updater|BaLeverk}} club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

==Club career==
Maza is a youth product of [[Reinickendorfer Füchse]], before moving to the youth academy of [[Hertha BSC]] in 2018. He started his senior career with the [[Hertha BSC II|Hertha reserves]] in 2022. On 27 April 2023, he signed his first professional contract with Hertha until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zeit.de/zustimmung?url=https://www.zeit.de/news/2023-04/27/nachwuchsspieler-ibrahim-maza-bleibt-bei-hertha|title=ZEIT ONLINE &#124; Lesen Sie zeit.de mit Werbung oder im PUR-Abo. Sie haben die Wahl.|website=www.zeit.de|access-date=1 May 2023|archive-date=1 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230501040257/https://www.zeit.de/zustimmung?url=https://www.zeit.de/news/2023-04/27/nachwuchsspieler-ibrahim-maza-bleibt-bei-hertha|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Hertha BSC as a substitute in a 2–0 [[Bundesliga]] loss to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] on 30 April 2023. With Hertha having already been relegated the previous week, Maza came on as a substitute and scored his first senior goal, equalising in a 2–1 away win against [[VfL Wolfsburg]] on 27 May 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.herthabsc.com/en/news/2023/05/match-report-wobbsc-2223|title=Hertha end the season with a 2-1 win in Wolfsburg|date=27 May 2023|website=Hertha BSC}}</ref>

On 1 May 2025, it was announced that Maza would join Bundesliga side [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] at the [[2024–25 Bayer 04 Leverkusen season|end of the season]]. He was transferred for a reported fee of €12 million, and he signed a contract until 2030.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-01 |title=Bayer Leverkusen signs highly rated teenager Ibrahim Maza from Hertha Berlin |url=https://apnews.com/article/leverkusen-maza-hertha-transfer-3463902e4c112b95c8be5a43200dba92 |access-date=2025-05-01 |website=AP News |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayer 04 verpflichtet Offensiv-Juwel Maza von Hertha BSC {{!}} Bayer04.de |url=https://www.bayer04.de/de-de/news/bayer04/bayer-04-verpflichtet-offensiv-juwel-maza-von-hertha-bsc |access-date=2025-05-01 |website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen Fussball GmbH |language=de}}</ref> As the year progressed, he scored his first goals for the club on 8 November by netting a brace in a 6–0 win over [[1. FC Heidenheim|Heidenheim]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-heidenheim-match-report-highlights-matchday-10-ibrahim-maza-34706 |title=Ibrahim Maza shines as Bayer Leverkusen run riot against Heidenheim |publisher=Bundesliga |date=8 November 2025 }}</ref> Later that month, on 25 November, he provided his first assist in the [[UEFA Champions League]] in a 2–0 away win over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/de/news/champions-league-pep-guardiola-charmed-by-ibrahim-maza-42007210 |title=Champions League: Pep Guardiola charmed by Ibrahim Maza |publisher=OneFootball |date=26 November 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Germany, Maza is of Algerian and Vietnamese descent. He holds Algerian and German nationalities. He is a former youth international, having played for Germany at the [[Germany national under-18 football team|U18]], [[Germany national under-19 football team|U19]], and [[Germany national under-20 football team|U20]] level.<ref name="Farid Kada rabah 2023">{{cite web | author=Farid Kada rabah | title=Un jeune joueur d'origine Algérienne de 17ans fait ses débuts en Bundesliga | website=DZBallon L'actu du football Algérien | date=2023-04-30 | url=https://dzballon.com/2023/04/30/un-jeune-joueur-dorigine-algerienne-de-17ans-fait-ses-debuts-en-bundesliga/ | access-date=2023-05-01}}</ref>

In October 2024, Maza was called up to the Algeria national football team for the first time for a pair of [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]] qualifiers against Togo. He made debut on the 89th minute of the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.faf.dz/eliminatoires-can-2025-la-liste-de-petkovic-pour-la-double-confrontation-face-au-togo/|title=ÉLIMINATOIRES CAN 2025 : LA LISTE DE PETKOVIC POUR LA DOUBLE CONFRONTATION FACE AU TOGO|publisher=FAF.dz|language=French|date=October 3, 2024|accessdate=October 3, 2024}}</ref>

